By UMMUL IDRIS BERLIN- Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau has announced the introduction of a bill aimed at tightening gun laws.The announcement is coming less than a week after a mass shooting at a primary school in the U.S. state of Texas that left 21 people dead.The new bill introduced by Trudeau’s government aims to end the private possession of handguns, outlawing their sale or purchase and banning handgun imports to Canada.Anyone found guilty of domestic violence will automatically lose their gun licences.In addition, the penalties for illegal weapons sales are to be increased.In Texas, an 18-year-old gunman caused carnage at a primary school last Tuesday.The rampage in the city of Uvalde has once again fuelled the debate on tightening U.S. gun laws.Republicans in particular have been vehemently opposed to stricter gun regulation for years. (dpa/NAN) By EMMANUEL YASHIM •Rehearsal for Victory Day Parade in Moscow •Russian President Vladimir Putin meets with Tver Region Governor Igor Rudenya, in Moscow Zaporizhzhia- Kremlin forces bombed a village school in eastern Ukraine killing about 60 people, President Volodymyr Zelenskiy said,.The bombing occurred as Russia prepared to mark the Monday anniversary… In "Foreign" Justin Trudeau, the Canadian Prime Minister has condemned Russia. The Prime Minister on Thursday condemned Russia’s “egregious” and “unprovoked” attack on Ukraine. He also called on Moscow to immediately withdraw from the country and saying its aggression “will not go unpunished.”“Canada condemns in the strongest possible terms Russia’s egregious attack… In "News" By Kevin Dougherty QUEBEC CITY   - Six people were killed and eight wounded when gunmen opened fire at a Quebec City mosque during Sunday night prayers, in what Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau called a "terrorist attack on Muslims". Police said two suspects had been arrested, but gave no… In "Foreign"